Welcome to Catable - the CATAlyst BLog Engine (by Perl cats).

Catable is a blog engine based on Catalyst, DBIx::Class and other technologies.
It is free and open source software (FOSS) that is licensed under the MIT/X11
Licence:

* http://www.opensource.org/licenses/mit-license.php

* http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MIT_License

Catable was written by Shlomi Fish ( http://www.shlomifish.org/ )
and Alastair Douglas ( http://search.cpan.org/~altreus/ ).

---------------------

Setting up:

Run "perl script/deploy.pl" to set up the SQLite database used by Catable.

Run script/app_catable_server.pl to test the application.

----------------------

Module::Buildy-stuff:

Run the following to test the application:

$ perl Build.PL

$ ./Build

$ ./Build test

(or if you Test::Run installed - "./Build runtest" )

You can also try running

./Build disttest (or "./Build distruntest").

